hmmmm so it's summertime here in murder beach and life is going extremely well. lots of changes, but i view change as a good thing.
about a month ago jess and i broke up. nothing major, no bad blood just had to happen. very mutual. sucks working w/ her since she's already fucking someone else, but oh well.
i then flew out to CA to look at a film school, and decided i am going there in january, so i can save up some money.
my band is probably breaking up, since our singer quit and i am moving.
the place i am interning at offered me a job until i leave, after i get done w/ my internship. so i will probably be working there and miyabis until i leave. it will be good b/c it will help me to get some experience under my belt.
i've been having fun this summer, just going out w/ friends, getting drunk and having house parties etc. next week i get to see AFI again, and the next day i might be going to see stretch arm strong, secret lives, and burns out bright in charleston.
anyways gotta jump in the shower in a few. hope everyone is doing well.
Wes
if i'm always going to feel alone, i might as well just be alone.

unless you've REALLY looked deep into my eyes. i want to show it to everyone, it would only take like an hour. in that hour i could sweat it out in front of you, i could bleed it out of every pour.some of you may have seen a hint of whats to come, but rest assured you've no idea. i want my passion to encloud everything like the air on a scorching SC summer afternoon. i want to change the world, change the people, change their mind's, even change the rocks if they'd listen. hopefully one day i'll bleed my beautiful rock and roll all over a stage for everyone i've ever known to see.

well anyways lets see, today was day 3 of band practice. it went well, i guess. i think we are going to keep looking for a singer and eventually demote will to just bass instead of bass and vocals. but our material is sounding good. josh and i are both doing decent background screams. hmmm x-mas was great. i get so spoiled every year for x-mas...like my parents and grandparents all went above and beyond this year...made me really grateful. well hey i am gonna run...jess should be here any minute. we've been dating almost 6 months now....still blows my mind

well things are good here. got done w/ school, i'm confident i'll have at least a 3.0 this semester b/c i know i got an A in digital photography and i got either an A or a high B in my online matgh class. anyways just working here a lot, only coming home for like 3 days or so for x-mas. jess starts working w/ me monday...at first i wasn't really looking forward to it, but i want the best for her, and right now whats best for her is being able to make her car payments etc. but she'll be all the way on the other side of the restaurant in the sushi bar so i'll barely ever see her while i'm at work. i just hope she doesn't get sucked in to restaurant work...it takes forever to get out of, trust me i know.

www.myspace.com/rowdymusic come and show us some love.
not only is josh married w/ a child now, he also has a 9-5 job...funny how things change. guess we're not 12 and 13 anymore...
and wed i'll be 24...and my grandparents are ocming in town. only like 2 weeks until i come home/ben folds/bright eyes/bouncing souls

so mckenna and josh found me on myspace. it's pretty cool, we talked online for a while last night. they're both coming down for the trio show next week. i'm really excited, but is it for the wrong reasons ?

so yeah i worked today from like 2pm-1am, but at least i made $170. monday jon jennings and his girlfriend julie are coming into town, i'm looking forward to it a lot etc. the other night jess and i went to see secret lives of the free masons play, they were really good.after that we drank at the bar and played some pool etc. i think we went out drinking like 3 times last week, it's been fun. it's weird being in a relationship again. it's been so long that i worry about fucking things up a lot. but i'm really crazy about her. i think i love her...not sure if i should tell her or not. i really hope we work out, we both don't want kids, and both would like to maybe adopt if it was ever an option. we also don't really believe in marriage. it's weird to find someone like that...someone i agree w/ on so many things and someone who is into the same things as me, but also different things such as art, and someone who is so fucking awesome at it.
well anyways i am going to run. going to grab some sleep so i can go eat lunch w/ my great fucking girlfriend before we both go to work tomorrow.

so yeah if youven't talked to me personally lately, then you've missed out on a lot. i started dating this girl named jess a few weeks ago, so far things are great. she's korean, and her brother is a chef where i work. she graduated from columbus art college or something like that w/ a degree in media illustration. she's 22, will be 23 in november, so i'm like a year and 24 days older than her or something like that.
also i'm in a new band w/ josh mcdowell we're both playing guitar, and possibly singing. eric from velvateen is playing bass and this guy named matthew is playing drums. we're still deciding on names, but i'm strongly pulling for the indoor kids. oh yeah josh mcdowell got married this past saturday, right now he's in cancun on his honeymoon. so yeah another one bites the dust. oh yeah anyone in s-burg who cares, jess and i will be there the 25th and 26th. and then jimmy eat world at the HOB the 28th and then i start school the 29th. taking design, computer graphics I, digital photography and then a internet math course. so yeah thats whats happening w/ me.
later kids

so instead of whining on here like usual, i thought i would do something productive and write about different albums that changed my life.
todays choice:

AFI- The Art of Drowning

I still remember the first time i heard AFI, it was on an old nitro comp called "go ahead punk make my day" or something like that. i absolutely HATED their songs on it. fast forward a few years and i am randomly taping videos off of mtv2 and i see AFI on and decide to videotape it, b/c i wasn't sure i'd ever see another video of theirs again. to make a long story short i watched their video for "days of the phoenix" OVER AND OVER again. i finally went to best buy and bought the cd. at first i really didn't like it, it was when i was more into poppy-punk, and had very limited experience w. any kind of hardcore. finally it grew on me, and i can now say it is one of my all-time favorite albums, definately my fav AFI album. i think i just really related to the dark imagery and undertones combined w/ the aggression. it was the first time i had ever heard anything like that. it was like a serious version of the misfits, w/ more talent. i would definately reccommend "Wester" to anyone. prob my fav AFI song ever.

And as I gently sip this drink,
I think about my lack of future,
And of all the places I could learn to fall in love.

I know I shouldn't waste my time,
I should have been better designed,
Therefore, some things still break.

I am wrecked. I am overblown.
I am also fed up with the fucking common cold!
When I just want to feel alive for the first time in my life,
I just want to feel attractive today.

so last night i went to hard rock w/ angel, cazzie and tammy. that was fun then we went to some bars at broadway, which sucked. we then went back to their condo so tammy could take out her contacts. after that we went to the shit shack and it was fucking dead.  so we had a drink and left. after that we ended up on the beach. cazzie and i got into a splashing match which resulted in a very sandy wrestling match. i had a blast though. honestly this great sense of calm came over me as soon as i put my feet in the water, i felt so happy i could burst. it was very weird, i don't know when the last time, or if i had ever felt like that was. anyways gonna run so i can pretend i'm getting ready for work.

so lonely days make me lonely and deppressed. i feel as if my old friends from s-burg don't even care if i exist. and i have like 2 people here that actually answer or return my phone calls. anyways off to finish tammy's b-day present. i sound like a little emo girl.

so thursday i went back to s-burg. ended up going to monterreys w/ jennings and brandon, then hanging out and playing soccer. after that met up w/ angel and we went to delaneys, saw brandon kimbrell for the first time in years. saw a bunch of other people i hadn't seen in years such as brooke blackwell, scott, and charlotte. we all got a little drunk and had a good time. went home, went to sleep then woke up and went to eat kanpai w/ my mom...i don't like it nearly as much as i used to, i guess eating/working at miyabis has spoiled me....after that went to my grandparents etc went to see josh flowes dad at the hospital...it was sad. he might be dying...after that went to eat at the clock w/ my parents then went to see footloose at the junior high. it was pretty good, the lead got off key every now and then but he could dance like a mofo. so after that i went to josh flowes and then went to the marriott for the alumni thing...it sucked and just cost me $$$. after that i went to angels and slept. woke up at 7:30 the next morning, drove to columbia for jeremy's graduation. i saw rachel vykukal for the first time in like a year. it was good seeing her i guess...we all went to the village idiot for lunch, then hung out at jeremy's apt and draNK champagne then we went to the mall etc. after that i took an hour nap at the rest area on the way to charleston. got to charleston at 10, met some guy named dan who is 36 at the westerberg show. he had actually gotten to see the replacements in '89. so anyways westerberg came out rockin' great charisma. right in the 2nd song he jumpoed into the crowd. he played freakin' everything. lots of songs off of stereo/mono. almost every replacements song you would want to hear. in the middle of the encore he had to piss so he went into the ladies restroom, after he got back he told all ofthe guys how good it was, and how we shoulod always "accidentally" go into the ladies room. so after that i left (he played for like 2 1/2 hours) and got home around 3:15. worked all day yesterday got there at 11, and left at 11. i only made $140, but i'lltake it. so yeah time to jump in the shower before my speech exam.

be there for a few days, then going to columbia for usc graduation and then to charleston to see paul westerberg with the floweman. working all day sunday (11am-midnight or so), then exams monday and tuesday. oh yeah i finished my music video it turned out really well. if you're lucky i'll show it to you one day.

last night i got called in, and got off around 12:30 again. we went back to jordans and drank a little bit. we met the most annoying gil ever. she talked like she was on AIM. she said things like "J/K!". so we took pics of ian picking his nose on her camera and a pic of him pretending to go down on a bottle in my pants. i ended up home around 5. so now i am going to start my research and go to work. i work monday and tuesday, school until 8:30pm wed, then i come home for the weekend.
